puls-g3 (0.7.0) buster; urgency=medium

  * Temperatures and sensor data refresh in real-time and used on different tabs
  * NVMe health percentage, power cycle count, and disk type (NVMe/SSD/HDD) shown on Disks tab
  * Sensors tried to be grouped by category (CPU, GPU, Memory, Disk, Fan, Other) with visual temperature bars
  * Enlarged gauges with borders and temperature display in info panel
  * Temperature row added to Memory tab details, not every computer gaves this info so dont expect much
  * Styled to match service status modal (larger, consistent borders)
  * Updated bollard to v0.19, fixed legacy client errors for newer Docker APIs
  * (I hope again) Fixed 0Hz/0Usage on AMD cards with hwmon sensor fallback
  * Added sysfs hwmon fallback when component label matching fails

